The Telegraph - Calcutta
 4-1 win for India
New Delhi: India defeated Argentina 4-1 in their opening match of the four-nation hockey tournament in Hamburg on Friday. India led 2-0 at half-time. Dilip Tirkey, Jugraj Singh, Baljit Singh Dhillon and Gagan Ajit Singh were the goal-scorers for India, according to information received here. Spain and hosts Germany are the other teams in the competition. (Pti)  Copyright 
